Program: Start the Week
Title: Political Writing: Joan Bakewell and Tim Montgomerie
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b01q8l31
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 28 Jan 2013
Start the Week Allan Little explores the legacy of George Orwell's essay Politics and the English Language. Joan Bakewell, Tim Montgomerie, Chris Mullin and Phil Collins discuss Orwell's warning that evasive language, euphemism and insincerity dominate political writing, and assess the impact of today's political diaries, blogging and tweeting. Producer: Katy Hickman. Show less